Deputy PM said he would block a new Coalition deal over welfare cuts . 
 He pledged to force David Cameron to impose new taxes on the wealthy . 
 The Liberal Democrats have called for £3bn of new welfare savings . 
 Coalition has slashed £20bn off the benefits bill in five years since 2010 . 
 Mr Clegg said Tories now 'lashing out' because they know they are losing . 
 Asked if he was proud of his record in power, he said: 'Hell yes'